---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="FPGA 32-Bit Calculator">
  <section class="p-8 sm:p-12 md:p-16 lg:p-24 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <a href="/#projects" class="text-sm text-gray-500 hover:underline">
      ← Back to Home
    </a>

    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900">
      FPGA 32-Bit Calculator
    </h1>


    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-6">
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">FPGA</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">8051 Assembly</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">Digital Design</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">Terasic DE10-Lite (MAX10 FPGA)</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg text-sm">VHDL</span>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
      Implemented a 32-bit calculator from scratch on DE10 Lite FPGA using 8051 assembly.
    </p>

    <br />

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <img src="/fpga1.jpeg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <img src="/fpgacalc1.png" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      <img src="/fpga3.jpeg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
    </div>

    
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: #00bfff; font-style: italic;">
        Project Outcomes
      </h2>
    
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Programmed a 32-bit arithmetic calculator using 8051 assembly on Altera DE10-Lite FPGA board</li>
        <li>Interfaced a 4×4 matrix keypad and seven-segment displays through memory-mapped GPIO for real-time user I/O</li>
        <li>Integrated integer overflow detection for 32-bit addition, multiplication, and decimal input conversion using processor carry flags and range validation</li>
        <li>Implemented integer square root algorithm to be used in right triangle solver by iterating Newton's method</li>
        <li>Optimized register allocation and stack usage to minimize memory footprint and improve execution efficiency in assembly</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">
      Summary
    </h2>

    <div class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
      Designed and implemented a 32-bit calculator on DE10 Lite FPGA using 8051 assembly, allowing for up to arithmetic operations (addition, subtraction, multiplication, division) and right triangle solving (by iterating Newton's method) on up to 10-digit packed BCD inputs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-8">
      <video
        class="w-full aspect-video rounded-md shadow-lg bg-black defer-play"
        controls
        muted
        playsinline
        preload="metadata"
        poster="/fpga1.jpeg"
        src="/fpga_vid.mp4"
      >
        <source src="/fpga_vid.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        Your browser does not support the video tag.
      </video>
    </div>

    <!-- FPGA clock section -->
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">
      FPGA 12-Hour Clock
    </h2>

    <div class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
      Another interesting project which I completed with my DE10-Lite board was programming a 12-hour settable alarm clock. This was done on Quartus Prime (Intel software) using VHDL as the hardware description language. The video below demonstrates the functionality of the clock.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-8">
      <video
        class="w-full aspect-video rounded-md shadow-lg bg-black defer-play"
        controls
        muted
        playsinline
        preload="metadata"
        poster="/fpga1.jpeg"
        src="/fpga_vidclock.mp4"
      >
        <source src="/fpga_vid.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        Your browser does not support the video tag.
      </video>
    </div>

      <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
          const vids = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('video.defer-play'));
          if (!vids.length) return;
          if ('IntersectionObserver' in window) {
            const io = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
              entries.forEach(entry => {
                const v = entry.target;
                if (entry.isIntersecting && entry.intersectionRatio >= 0.5) {
                  v.play().catch(() => {});
                } else {
                  v.pause();
                }
              });
            }, { threshold: 0.5 });
            vids.forEach(v => { v.pause(); io.observe(v); });
          } else {
            vids.forEach(v => v.play().catch(() => {}));
          }
        });
      </script>

    <!-- Fig 1–2 -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-8">
      <figure>
          <img
            src="/fpgaclock1.png"
            alt="Quartus code"
            class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg"
          />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Quartus VHDL program
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
          <img
            src="/fpgaclock2.png"
            alt="FPGA Clock"
            class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg"
          />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Hardware Description
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

  </section>
</Layout>
